{"sections":[],"relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Inherits From","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"],"type":"inheritsFrom","kind":"relationships"},{"title":"Conforming Types","type":"conformingTypes","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data structure that represents a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"condition. Threads can block on a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond"},{"text":" if they find a certain","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"condition to be false. If other threads change the state of this","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"condition they signal the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond"},{"text":", and that causes the waiting","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"threads to be woken up."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/condprotocol"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"CondProtocol"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"PointerWrapper","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Consider the following example of a shared variable.  One or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"threads can wait for data to be published to the variable and when","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"another thread publishes the data, it can signal one of the waiting","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"threads to wake up to collect the data.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Here is an example for using GCond to block a thread until a condition","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is satisfied:"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(C Language Example):","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"C","code":["  gpointer current_data = NULL;","  GMutex data_mutex;","  GCond data_cond;","","  void","  push_data (gpointer data)","  {","    g_mutex_lock (&data_mutex);","    current_data = data;","    g_cond_signal (&data_cond);","    g_mutex_unlock (&data_mutex);","  }","","  gpointer","  pop_data (void)","  {","    gpointer data;","","    g_mutex_lock (&data_mutex);","    while (!current_data)","      g_cond_wait (&data_cond, &data_mutex);","    data = current_data;","    current_data = NULL;","    g_mutex_unlock (&data_mutex);","","    return data;","  }"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Whenever a thread calls "},{"code":"pop_data()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" now, it will wait until"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"current_data is non-"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", i.e. until some other thread"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"has called ","type":"text"},{"code":"push_data()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The example shows that use of a condition variable must always be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"paired with a mutex.  Without the use of a mutex, there would be a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"race between the check of ","type":"text"},{"code":"current_data","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" by the while loop in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pop_data()"},{"text":" and waiting. Specifically, another thread could set","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"current_data","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" after the check, and signal the cond (with nobody"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"waiting on it) before the first thread goes to sleep. ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"specifically useful for its ability to release the mutex and go"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to sleep atomically.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is also important to use the "},{"code":"g_cond_wait()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_wait_until()"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"functions only inside a loop which checks for the condition to be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"true.  See ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_wait()"},{"text":" for an explanation of why the condition may","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"not be true even after it returns.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is allocated in static storage then it can be used"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"without initialisation.  Otherwise, you should call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_init()"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"on it and ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_cond_clear()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" when done."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" should only be accessed via the g_cond_ functions.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GCond"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef","isActive":true},{"text":" as a lighweight, ","type":"text"},{"code":"unowned","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Protocol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"CondProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"symbolKind":"protocol","externalID":"s:4GLib12CondProtocolP","title":"CondProtocol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CondProtocol","kind":"identifier"}]},"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol"},"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol\/broadcast()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol\/clear()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol\/free()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol\/init_()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol\/signal()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol\/timedWait(mutex:absTime:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol\/wait(mutex:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol\/waitUntil(mutex:endTime:)"],"title":"Instance Methods"}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/CondProtocol/clear()":{"title":"clear()","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol\/clear()","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"clear","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/condprotocol\/clear()","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Frees the resources allocated to a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_init()"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/CondRef":{"title":"CondRef","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/condref","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CondRef","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"CondRef"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data structure that represents a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"condition. Threads can block on a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" if they find a certain"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"condition to be false. If other threads change the state of this"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":